OL,3,CKing shows off language skills during
OL,4,CIsle of Man visit
OL,6,FThe King showed off his linguistic
OL,7,Fflair during his first official visit
OL,8,Fto the Isle of Man as monarch, joking
OL,9,Fthat he hoped he was not "massacring"
OL,10,Fthe island's native language.
OL,12,FKing Charles spoke in Manx, a language
OL,13,Fthat has seen a recent revival, during
OL,14,Fa special sitting of the island's
OL,15,Fparliament, Tynwald, and later
OL,16,Fswitched to French while chatting with
OL,17,Fa native speaker among the crowds
OL,18,Foutside.
OL,26,@qD@ZOUqD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
